This spontaneous report was received from a consumer or other non health professional (patient's grandmother) 
and concerns a 36-months-old male patient from the United States: 017437200A.
The patient's height, weight and medical history were not reported. 
The patient was treated with paracetamol (oral suspension, oral, unspecified dose and frequency) initiated on 18-
DEC-2015 for accidental ingestion and fever. Concomitant medications were not reported. 
On 18-DEC-2015, the patient had product to help with a fever. Later, the patient opened the bottle and poured the 
product out (product not child proof( packaging complaint)) he also put some in the cup. The consumer 
(grandmother) was unsure of how much or if any was consumed by the patient (possible accidental ingestion).
Action taken with paracetamol was not applicable.
The outcome for product not child proof (packaging complaint) and possible accidental ingestion was not reported. 
This report was associated with a product complaint and product quality complaint number not reported.
This report was not serious.